name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: Over time, people will go back to work, restaurants will reopen, and things will go back to normal. We look forward to working together as one region to tackle this challenge together.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: Phasing in sectors of our economy will be most effective when we work together as a region. This doesn’t mean our economy will reopen all at once, or that every state will take the same steps at the same time. But close coordination will ensure we get this right.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
We will closely examine at least these four factors when determining when best to reopen our economy:

➡️ Sustained control of the rate of new infections and hospitalizations. 

➡️ Enhanced ability to test and trace.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: Our number one priority when analyzing when best to reopen our economy is the health and safety of our citizens. We will make decisions based on facts, science, and recommendations from experts in health care, business, labor, and education.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: We look forward to working with experts and taking a fact-based, data-driven approach to reopening our economy in a way that protect families from the spread of #COVID19.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: Today, we are announcing that Michigan, Ohio, Wisconsin, Minnesota, Illinois, Indiana, and Kentucky will work in close coordination to reopen our economies in a way that prioritizes our workers’ health.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: Here in the Midwest, we are bound by our commitment to our people & the community. We recognize that our economies are all reliant on each other, & we must work together to safely reopen them so hardworking people can get back to work & businesses can get back on their feet.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: We are doing everything we can to protect the people of our states and slow the spread of #COVID19, and we are eager to work together to mitigate the economic crisis this virus has caused in our region.
